        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-09-16 15:46:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nI note that we have code #ifdef CPU_AFFINITY only in socklnd.  If this is a useful feature maybe other lnd's should have something like it too?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "06420c9546a48fe69da3e69a5f72870045084bfa",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 251,
        "name": "Bob Glossman",
        "email": "bob.glossman@intel.com",
        "username": "bogl",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-09-16 15:54:20.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI see that set_cpus_allowed_ptr() is defined and exists in the kernel whether or not the kernel has CONFIG_SMP in the config.  If you are trying to make CPU_AFFINTITY conditional on CONFIG_SMP set_cpus_allowed_ptr() may not be the best choice.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "06e7bd12e808a3db45615bd0d583f8bbe769065d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 198,
        "name": "Minh Diep",
        "email": "mdiep@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "mdiep"
      },
      "date": "2013-09-16 16:20:03.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI am adding Liang into this. Liang, I don't see anything useful in CPU_AFFINITY enable, only setting for enable_irq_affiinity which is not used anymore.\n\nQuestion: Can I cleanup/remove CPU_AFFINITY and enable_irq_affinity?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
